<Content>Great location, staff, atmosphere My husband and I spent a week at Cram. We were looking for a hotel which would be near the city centre but not noisy or too touristy. The hotel is in a classic building but is modern and is only 5 minutes walk from the university and 10 miutes from las Rambas. So an easy walk to see the sights and go out at night. The rooms are fairly spacious and there is plenty of storage. Every room has free internet connection and a great selection of films on demand for free. The beds are comfy and the shower gorgeous. On the roof is a small swimming pool (about 16 foot by 6 foot) but it is enough to cool yourself off in and sun loungers after a hard day sightseeing. There is a bar there as well but it wasn't open late when we were there. We didn't eat breakfast but it is served on the roof and looked nice. There is also a very reasonably priced Michelin starred restaurant on the ground floor.The staff are friendly and the place is spotless. I couldn't recommend a better place to stay for a relaxing, fun, holiday. 
