<Content>Warmly recommended ! We went to Barcelona for three days, and booked Cram (based on research on quite luxury/trendy hotel at still realistic price). Experience was excellent : it started before our stay : we bombarded the hotel with zillions of e-mail questions to make sure we would have exactly what we want, and they responded smoothly and efficiently to all of our queries.Unlike what some reviews suggest (and made us a bit afraid before leaving), the service was really excellent and friendly, warm. The place is very nice, and even if the rooftop pool isn't the pool you would book the hotel for, the rroftop is a nice place to breakfast, have a drink, sunbathe... (unfortunately, the sun wasn't very present this week-end).Funny to read the previous review, as indeed a big plus was for us the darkness of the curtains (we could sleep very late and when we wake up it still was dark as if in the middle of the night : great when you want to rest a bit without children waking you up very early...:-)).And the last day, they agreed us to check-out only at 1pm (time we had to leave to the airport) : this kind of flexibility makes life that smoother....And honestly : the place is NOT far away from Passeig de Gracia, Ramblas, Casa Battlo etc : only a 5-10 minutes walk; so for us, very well placed !!!And last but not least : having a dinner at GAIG restaurant is not cheap, but what a spectacularly nice gastronomic experience !!Thanks to all of the Cram's team, and see you again, undoubtedly. 
